Seven policemen lost their lives on Sunday evening along Kaduna-Zaria road. According to a military personnel who was close to the scene of the accident, the speeding 18 seater vehicle somersaulted around Jaji Military Cantonment. DAILY POST could not ascertain where the policemen were coming from, but it was learnt they were heading towards Zaria from Kaduna when the accident happened. According to the military personnel who refused to disclose his name, “It was a terrible accident because I counted about seven bodies of policemen in the middle of the road. “Two were seriously injured while others survived.” Kaduna Police Public Relations Officer, (PPRO) ASP Muhammed Jalige said the Command has sent a team of policemen to the scene to get details of what happened.